query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `auth_otp_logs` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT NOT NULL,
  `userId` int NOT NULL,
  `phone` varchar(20) NOT NULL,
  `otpCode` varchar(6) NOT NULL,
  `status` enum('sent','verified','expired','failed') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'sent',
  `failedAttempts` int NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  `sentAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT (now()),
  `verifiedAt` timestamp NULL,
  `expiresAt` timestamp NOT NULL,
  `ipAddress` varchar(45) NULL,
  CONSTRAINT `auth_otp_logs_id` PRIMARY KEY(`id`),
  CONSTRAINT `auth_otp_logs_userId_fk` FOREIGN KEY (`userId`) REFERENCES `users`(`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  INDEX `auth_otp_logs_user_idx` (`userId`),
  INDEX `auth_otp_logs_phone_idx` (`phone`),
  INDEX `auth_otp_logs_status_idx` (`status`),
  INDEX `auth_otp_logs_expires_at_idx` (`expiresAt`)
);
